  "info": {
    "overview": {
      "aboutTheApp": "About the app",
      "aboutTheAppSection": "Application Routio was developed as part of the bachelor's thesis at the Faculty of Information Technology, Brno University of Technology, under the supervision of Ing. Jiří Hynek, Ph.D. The application supports both unimodal routing, where only one transport mode is used, and multimodal routing, combining multiple modes within a single journey.",
      "supportedModes": "Supported transport modes",
      "whyApp": "Motivation and Background",
      "whyAppSection1": "Every day mobility is an essential part of people's lives. People travel by car, public transport, walking, or by alternative options such as shared bicycles.",
      "whyAppSection2": "As cities continue to grow and mobility demands increase, there is a rising need to combine different modes of transport. Existing solutions often do not provide sufficient support for integrating cycling and shared cycling into multimodal route planning.",
      "whyAppSection3": "The purpose of this work was therefore to create a unified solution that enables the combination of multiple transport modes within a single journey.",
      "external": "External services and data",
      "externalSectionDB": "Open public transport data of the South Moravian Region in GTFS and GTFS-RT formats",
      "externalSectionOTP": "A routing engine for planning journeys using public transport, walking, and cycling",
      "externalSectionLissy": "API providing route shapes and historical delay information for public transport services",
      "externalSectionNextbike": "Real-time information about shared bicycles available at Nextbike stations",
      "externalSectionOSM": "Open map data and information about transport infrastructure",
      "contact": "Contact",
      "contactSection": "If you have any questions, comments or suggestions regarding the application, please feel free to contact me by email:"
    },
